        "require_dhcp_relay": false,</p><p> "domain_suffix_pattern":
        "{subnet_name}.cloud.global.com",</p><p> "hostname_pattern":
        "{instance_name}-{ip_address}"</p><p>
        }</p><p>]</p><b>/etc/neutron/infoblox_members.conf</b><p>Create
        /etc/neutron.infooblox_members.conf with the following line to include IOA VM IP
        address.</p><p>[{"ipv4addr": "10.200.51.240", "name": "infoblox.localdomain"}]</p><p>
        NOTE:Here 10.200.51.240 is the CLM IP of the IOA VM running in ESX environment which was
        provided during IOA configuration</p><b>Verification</b><p>Login to Infoblox
        Dashboard</p><p>Traverse to <i>Administration &gt;&gt; Network views </i>and see if the
        subnet pool got created</p><p><image
          href="https://wiki.hpcloud.net/download/attachments/54738286/IPAMUtilization.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1444860464000&amp;api=v2"
          id="image_svd_rfz_5t"/></p><p> </p><p> </p><b>Patching HOSCG-NEUTRON with
        Infobloxchanges</b><p>Steps to apply infoblox patch on to the Neutron source code (<b>This
          needs to be done only while creating the hoscg-neutron.deb and need not be executed while
          installing the package</b> ) :</p><p>1. Checkout latest neutron source code from the
        branch hp/cg/stable/2.0 git clone <xref href="http://git.dc.usa.hp.com/openstack/neutron"
          format="html" scope="external">http://git.dc.usa.hp.com/openstack/neutron</xref> -b
        hp/cg/stable/2.0</p><p>2. Get inside the neutron directory - cd neutron</p><p>3. Apply with
        infoblox patch, on to the source code. Patch file hp-poc-20151016-full is available at
        15.242.209.8 E:\sFTP\cg-hos-2-0-builds\patches\build022\Infoblox\ patch -p1 &lt;
        path_to_patch_file ex: patch -p1 &lt; /root/hp-poc-20151016-full.patch Make sure that no
        Failure/Error messaages are displayed, while running the last command.</p><p>4. Add the
        following lines to MANIFEST.in </p><p>include
        neutron/db/migration/alembic_migrations/versions/172ace2194db_infoblox_net_view_to_network_id.py
        </p><p>include
        neutron/db/migration/alembic_migrations/versions/33150f5993b6_infoblox_management_net_handling.py
        </p><p>include neutron/db/migration/alembic_migrations/versions/78d27e9172_infoblox_db_v2.py
        </p><p>include
        neutron/db/migration/alembic_migrations/versions/d9841b33bd_add_infoblox_member_type.py
        </p><p>include
        neutron/db/migration/alembic_migrations/versions/256b90dd9824_multiple_dhcp_members.py</p><p>5.
        The current folder (neutron) now has the neutron source code from the branch
        hp/cg/stable/2.0 + infoblox source code patch. This source code has to be used for creating
        the debian package for hoscg-neutron.</p><p> </p></p>
    
